==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worsted
<hw>Worst"ed</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Worsted</ets>, now spelled <ets>Worstead</ets>, a town in Norfolk,
England; for <ets>Worthstead</ets>. See <er>Worth</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
and <er>Stead</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Well-twisted yarn spun of long-staple wool which has
been combed to lay the fibers parallel, used for carpets, cloth,
hosiery, gloves, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fine and soft woolen yarn, untwisted or lightly
twisted, used in knitting and embroidery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wort</ent>⟦br⟧
